// Hotfix: added 217 missing opposite relation fields (215 list back-refs + 2 forward fields). No FK, index, enum, or constraint changes.
// =============================================================================
//  PRISMA SCHEMA — V1.2 MERGED FINAL
// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
//  Version       : 1.2 MERGED FINAL
//  Status        : FINAL — authoritative single source of truth
//  Date          : 2026-06-12
//  Supersedes    : Prisma Schema V1.0 (unified)
//                  Prisma Schema V1.1 FINAL (REJECTED — see audit below)
//  Aligned with  : Database Dictionary V2.2 FINAL (additive deltas only)
//                  RBAC Matrix V2.2 FINAL
//                  API Specification V2.2 FINAL
//                  Frontend Navigation Architecture V1.1.1 FINAL
//  Provider      : PostgreSQL
//
//  HOTFIX (validation): Building relation removed from Room/Lab; `building`
//  is a free-text VARCHAR(64) field per Database Dictionary V2.2 (no
//  Building model exists). Totals unchanged: 124 models, 116 enums.
//
//  AUDIT BANNER
//  ------------
//  Prisma Schema V1.1 FINAL failed the schema-integrity audit
//  (see prisma-schema-diff-v1-to-v1.1-FINAL.md — verdict: CRITICAL DATA
//  LOSS RISK). It removed 89 models and 102 enums covering RBAC,
//  Authentication, LMS, Timetabling, Placement, Research, Files,
//  Certificates, Transcripts, Wallet and multi-campus topology without
//  changelog justification. V1.2 MERGED FINAL re-baselines on V1 and
//  applies ONLY the 9 approved V2.2 additive models.
//
//  INTEGRITY STATEMENT
//  -------------------
//  - Zero V1 model removals.
//  - Zero V1 enum removals.
//  - Zero V1 relation, index or constraint removals.
//  - 9 new models, 5 new enums, and a small set of additive back-relation
//    fields on User / Institute / WorkflowInstance / Faculty / Student /
//    Exam are the ONLY changes vs V1.
//
//  EXPECTED TOTALS
//  ---------------
//  Models : 124 (V1: 115  +  Overlay: 9)
//  Enums  : 116 (V1: 111  +  Overlay: 5)
//
//  APPROVED V2.2 OVERLAY (verbatim, FK-rewired where necessary)
//  ------------------------------------------------------------
//    Models:  IdempotencyKey, FeatureFlag, InstituteFeatureFlag,
//             ApprovalEscalation, MentorAssignment, MentorSession,
//             OnlineExamMedia, I18nString, NotificationProviderConfig
//    Enums:   IdempotencyState, FeatureRolloutType, EscalationState,
//             OnlineExamMediaKind, NotificationProvider
//
//  CONFLICT RESOLUTION APPLIED
//  ---------------------------
//  - MentorAssignment.mentorId / MentorSession.runByMentorId FKs were
//    rewired from Employee (V1.1-only) to Faculty (V1 canonical). The
//    business contract is preserved: a Faculty row carrying a UserRole
//    with mentor_addon scope acts as a mentor.
//  - OnlineExamMedia.examId references V1's Exam model (which exists in
//    V1 unchanged); no rewire needed.
//  - I18nString has no Institute FK in the V1.1 source, so no
//    Institute back-relation was added. It is a global lookup table.
//  - All overlay enum values are lower_snake_case; this matches V1.1's
//    convention for the new enums and does not conflict with any V1 enum.
//  - Money columns inside the 9 overlay models use Decimal(12,2)
//    (rupees in DB) per V2.2; V1 money columns retain their V1 types.
//
//  ITEMS PRISMA CANNOT EXPRESS (live in migrations / docs)
//  -------------------------------------------------------
//    - Partial unique indexes (WHERE deleted_at IS NULL, mentor active,
//      idempotency live)             → prisma/migrations/_partial_indexes.sql
//    - RLS policies                  → prisma/migrations/_policies/*.sql
//    - GRANT / REVOKE                → prisma/migrations/_grants/*.sql
//    - public.has_role(_uid, _role)  → prisma/migrations/_functions/has_role.sql
//    - pg_cron schedules
//        * idempotency_keys GC (15m)
//        * approval_escalations scan (5m)
//                                    → prisma/migrations/_cron/*.sql
// =============================================================================

generator client {
  provider        = "prisma-client-js"
  previewFeatures = ["postgresqlExtensions", "fullTextSearch"]
}

datasource db {
  provider   = "postgresql"
  url        = env("DATABASE_URL")
  extensions = [pgcrypto, citext, pg_trgm]
}

